ONE OUTLET W/FLANGE, GAUGE COCK, BLEED VALVE AND VR (SOLID), OTHER SIDE W/TWO 2-1/16 5M VG-300 VALVES AND DOUBLE BLOCK AND BLEED VALVE. MAXIMUM WORKING PRESSURE AS PART OF SYSTEM = 3,112 PSI (LIMITED BY INTERNAL 13-3/8 CASING COLLAPSE PRESSURE 0.8 X 3,890 PSI).

Assemble casing head per A114235-14C26 shipping configuration drawing (page 2 of 3) and below process notes and perform post conductor weld FAT including VR plug backseat test per A140761 and A951925-23 drawing.

1. REFER TO SUB-LEVEL UNITIZATION PN A114235-9C26 FOR SHIPMENT ARRANGEMENT COMPONENTS

2. LINE TO BE PAINTED AROUND CIRCUMFERENCE WITH BLACK AEROSOL AT LOCATION SHOWN. APPROX 1 INCH WIDE LINE, THE CENTRE OF WHICH LIES DIMENSION SHOWN. (THIS IS A VISUAL INDICATOR FOR LANDING THE HEAD TO DECK LEVEL DURING INSTALLATION).
']

Workscope:
CARRY OUT SCOPE AS PER SO 44000951136 WO 71 NOTE 3:

"Locate Tbg Bonnets & inspect all C77 3/8â MP Autoclave port threads cleanliness ensuring no paint debris etc is present, where required carefully tap out the thread & with both needle valves closed blow out threads with shop air. Open both needle valves & blow shop air via the 3/8â MP Autoclave port ensuring no water or debris exits from the Tbg Hgr Bridge Nipple ports on the bottom of the Tbg bonnet, close all C77 block needle valves again. Locate Nexen supplied 3/8â Autoclave x Â¼â Tube fittings, apply a small amount of Never Seize compound to the 3/8â Autoclave thread fitting, screw a fitting into each C77 block & torque to 20 ft/lbs. Remove the fittings to confirm all threads are good, report any problems. Re-fit the 3/8â Autoclave fittings into each C77 block & torque to 20 ft/lbs & leave in place, prepare the Tbg Bonnets for shipping offshore ensuring the pre-shipping checklists have been completed.
Record all C77 block S/Nâs as fitted to the Tbg Bonnets."

Descriptions:
['SURFACE XMT


As per note 1 on work order 
Locate tree & remove tree cap, open all production bore valves. Visually inspect tree production bore for excess valve grease & drift bore with a 5â drift, with measurement confirm drift goes fully through the tree, remove drift & inspect for excess grease, if excess grease is present clean out & re-drift. Close all valves. Fit Nexen / Altus supplied P64 Hub x 9â Otis X-Over C/W gasket & torque connection.
Fit offset tree lift cap & secure tree into shipping frame.
Locate Tree Cap, Needle Valve & Pressure Gauge & fit into the shipping frame storage box, prepare assembly for shipping.
']
